  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Start your day well with a full buffet breakfast served between 7.30am and 10am. You'll have a wide selection pastries, cheeses, cereals and fruit to choose from and cooked breakfasts are available on request.</p>
<p>Dinner is taken in the authentic mountain style restaurant, complete with arch ceilings and original paintings and carvings by local artists. Enjoy a four-course meal starting with a buffet of antipasti and finishing on a high with a delicious home made dessert or help yourself to the cheese buffet. There's also an <span>à la carte menu that you can choose from (payable locally)</span>.</p>
<p>There's a great atmosphere in the hotel's bar. It's in the historic part of the building dating back to the 1920's. Catch up on the days events with friends and family over a glass of wine, beer or cocktail.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>As soon as you walk into the Hotel Castor you'll get a warm welcome. The family have been running the hotel for four generations and greet each guest as though they know them. Set at the end of the main street - Route Ramey, you are short walk away from the range of cafes, bars and shops Champoluc has to offer. The Crest gondola is a short walk away, however the hotel offers a shuttle service so you can easily get onto the slopes each day. </p>
<h2>Ski Shuttle</h2>
<p>It's ideally located in the historic centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/090d2ea7dadc4d03ba25ba2f7aaac686" href="/{localLink:umb://document/090d2ea7dadc4d03ba25ba2f7aaac686}" title="Champoluc">Champoluc</a> and the hotel runs a shuttle service to the lifts in the morning and afternoon. You can also reach the main Crest gondola in ten minutes or so on foot. Along the main street you can find a variety of cosy cafes, bars and a variety sport shops. </p>
<h2>Live Music</h2>
<p>There's a cosy and comfortable ambiance throughout the hotel. You could spend hours relaxing, reading, drinking and socialising in the lounge bar. Once a week there's live music - the place really comes alive. When it comes to dinner, you'll be well-fuelled for your week in the mountains. Enjoy a hearty Italian, four-course meal in the authentic mountain setting of the hotel restaurant.</p>
<h2>The Extra Mile</h2>
<p>The hotel offer a homely base for your winter holiday, as well as some extras that make for fantastic, memorable experiences. From exploring the back-country with a professional alpine guide, to Pilates classes available, and our personal favourite; the opportunity to sample some local wines in a group tasting session (all payable locally).</p>]]></description>
